I just returned from 5 days in the desert and it was 5 days of many firsts.
.
My first 5 1/2 hour bike ride.
.
First time seeing a full rainbow in that valley.
.
First time I only jumped off my bike twice while going down a route I think is the hardest.
.
My biggest “first” was completing Joe’s Ridge.
.
While I know lots of people who can ride that decent with their eyes closed, it’s got a quick and steep ridge that scares the bleep out of me and I’ve feared and hated that ridge, quickly jumping off and walking my bike, every time I’ve ridden that trail.
.
But I know what fear does. It keeps you stuck. It doesn’t let you grow or move forward. And it sure doesn’t let you move on to bigger, more challenging and better things. So while my legs were shaking and I almost cried before I attempted it ( 🙈🤗) I plunged ahead. Not falling. Not failing. And feeling super proud of myself afterwards. And it would have been OK if I did fall. I think. 🤕
.
The thing is we all do courageous acts every day. We face fears, sometimes letting them get the best of us, hopefully ignoring them and moving ahead anyways. It takes courage to carve our own path. Change the things we can’t accept. It takes guts to stay or leave a bad job or relationship. Move a home or a life. I’m in awe of my community and how they live, raise their children or choose to go solo. Just getting up in the morning can sometimes be a courageous act.
.
This Spring I launched the Joe’s Ridge inspired hat to remind us that life is both beautiful and scary. But to fully embrace it means to always choose love, inspiration and courage over hate and fear. And to always ride or walk that trail that moves you forward.
.

Well, this stinks. Had a solid lap going with @desertmonkey99 at the @cbbfruita shop ride on #18rd but then overcooked a corner on #joesridge and went down HARD. Literally knocked the wind out of myself - struggling to breathe on the way home prompted us to head for the ER where imaging revealed a badly broken rib and partially collapsed lung. Currently at St. Mary's under observation. Should be out tomorrow, but my plans for the next month or so just got royally screwed. 😥

Thanks to my buds who helped me off the trail and of course @imoir for getting me where I needed to go! 🏨

If anyone needs me I'll be in la-la land. 💊💉
